<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Eupatorium paniculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schrad., Ind. Sem. Hort. Acad. Gott. 2. 1832; Linnaea 8, Litt. 26. 1833, hom. illeg., non Miller 1768. Photo from G-DC. Herbarium seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="69">With the habit of the typical variety, but differing by the rather abrupt short acuminatie tips on leaf blades, stipitate glands on the peduncles and branches of the inflorescence, and by the not or scarcely paler ribs on the submature achenes.</paragraph>
